  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I just finished highschool. What should I do while waiting to get in to a university?",
  "response": "Congratulations on finishing high school! Here are some productive and fulfilling activities you can consider while waiting to enter university:\n\n1. **Work or Intern**: Look for part-time jobs or internships related to your intended field of study. This can provide valuable experience and help you build a professional network.\n\n2. **Take Online Courses**: Platforms like Coursera, edX, and Khan Academy offer various courses. You can explore subjects related to your future studies or develop new skills, such as coding, photography, or foreign languages.\n\n3. **Volunteer**: Find local organizations or charities that resonate with you. Volunteering not only helps others but also enhances your resume and can provide valuable experiences and skills.\n\n4. **Travel**: If possible, consider traveling. This can broaden your perspective, expose you to new cultures, and help you learn more about yourself.\n\n5. **Read**: Dive into books\u2014fiction, non-fiction, or academic texts\u2014to expand your knowledge and improve your critical thinking and writing skills.\n\n6. **Prepare for University**: Familiarize yourself with your future coursework. You could start reading textbooks or materials related to your major, or brush up on relevant skills.\n\n7. **Network**: Attend workshops, seminars, or conferences in fields that interest you. Networking with professionals can provide insights into your future career and help you form valuable connections.\n\n8. **Develop Hobbies**: Use this time to explore and develop hobbies or interests you might not have had time for during high school. Whether it's painting, playing an instrument, or sports, engaging in hobbies is fulfilling.\n\n9. **Exercise**: Prioritize your physical health. Join a gym, take fitness classes, or participate in outdoor activities. Staying active can improve your mental health and well-being.\n\n10. **Work on Personal Projects**: If you have ideas for personal projects\u2014like a blog, YouTube channel, or a small business\u2014now could be a great time to start.\n\n11. **Plan for Your Future**: Reflect on your goals and aspirations. Consider how you want to spend your university years and what you want to achieve afterwards.\n\n12. **Connect with Future Classmates**: Join forums or social media groups related to your university or programs of interest. Meeting future classmates can help ease any anxiety you might have about starting university.\n\nMake sure to find a balance of productivity and relaxation as you transition into this new chapter of your life. Enjoy this time!",
